tldr: The user requested a comprehensive aesthetic review and improvement for
  their sleep questionnaire app. The agent implemented a new sleep-themed color
  palette, redesigned the main form layout and intro section, updated all UI
  components and form sections for visual consistency, and fixed a console error
  related to null input values.
overview: The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app. The agent began by conducting a thorough code review of the
  existing styling. A new, calming sleep-themed color palette was introduced
  using OKLCH, along with custom CSS utility classes for gradients and shadows.
  The main questionnaire form layout was redesigned with decorative background
  elements, an improved progress indicator, and a subtle star pattern on card
  headers. The intro section was transformed with a hero component and
  interactive feature cards. All core UI components (checkboxes, radio buttons,
  sliders, progress bars, and cards) received updated styling for a more
  polished and cohesive look. Furthermore, all 14 individual questionnaire
  sections were updated to use the new card-style groupings and consistent
  typography. During the review, a console error related to null values being
  passed to input components was identified and fixed. Finally, the agent
  addressed further aesthetic refinements by updating alert colors to align with
  the new theme and increasing the border opacity of section grouping boxes. The
  changes were committed in logical, atomic units.
